### Bean Lifecycle Annotations
*   `@PostConstruct`: Method called immediately after dependency injection.
*   `@PreDestroy`: Method called right before the bean is removed from the context.

```java
@Component
public class DatabaseConnector {
    @PostConstruct
    public void init() {
        System.out.println("Connection established!");
    }

    @PreDestroy
    public void cleanup() {
        System.out.println("Connection closed safely.");
    }
}
```

### Core REST Best Practices
*   Use HTTP methods semantically: `GET` (retrieve), `POST` (create), `PUT` (full update), `PATCH` (partial update), `DELETE` (remove).
*   Use plural nouns for resource paths: `/api/v1/users` instead of `/api/v1/getUser`.
*   Use standard status codes: `200 OK`, `201 Created`, `400 Bad Request`, `401 Unauthorized`, `404 Not Found`, `500 Server Error`.

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/v1/products")
public class ProductController {
    @GetMapping("/{id}")
    public ResponseEntity<Product> getProduct(@PathVariable Long id) {
        return ResponseEntity.ok(productService.findById(id));
    }
}
```
